Douglas Bader lost his legs in a flying accident in 1931 . 
  He was shot down over France in 1941 and ended up in a German prison camp in Warburg . 
  Bader was involved in a mass break-out that pre-dated the Great Escape in 1944 immortalised in The Great Escape . 
  The fighter ace’s story is to be told in a Hollywood film dubbed ‘The First Great Escape’ It is based on a book on the escape by historian Mark Felton called Zero Night . 
  The rights to the book have been bought by producers of Saving Banks . 
 